Preheat broiler. Stir oil, rosemary and garlic in small saucepan over low heat until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Arrange bread slices on small baking sheet. Broil until golden, about 1 minute. Turn toasts over. Brush with oil mixture, dividing equally. Broil toasts until golden and crisp, about 1 minute. Serve toasts warm.